Introduction

This class requires access to two pieces of software, R and RStudio. These are both open source and freely available, and I highly recommend installing them on your own computer (see the other document for installation instructions). If this is not possible, you can access these through the CSBS virtual lab. For this, you will need to install Citrix workspace, and log on using your University credentials. A full description of how to do this can be found here.

Once you have connected, you should see a window with a set of available applications. Look for RStudio (a light blue circle with R in the middle), and click this. This should open a window that looks something like this:

Please do not hesitate to contact me if you are having trouble accessing this.
